The four-song EP ‘Melodie’ is the bedroom production of Cor Allen. Soul-searching after the end of a relationship and a band, he found peace playing harmonium for a spiritual Guru. The Guru once said “everyone is sinless in their true nature” and it resonated. Cor rounded up borrowed gear, cheap synthesizers, and guitars inherited from his late father. He painted the sounds of his classic pop songwriting influences to record for the first time on his own. The result was eight songs glowing with earworm melodies and analogue warmth. Once finishing recording and needing a fresh start, Cor left his bedroom in Pittsburgh, PA with a car full of music gear to start Sinless in the band-mecca of Portland, OR. Cor got his musical start in Portland playing lead guitar for Portland psych-folk wizard Jackson Boone until Sinless was fully formed. The band features members Pete Bosack, who mixed and mastered both of the Sinless EP’s, on bass (also of Mothertapes and Loch Lomond), John Walsh (formerly Palace Fiction) on guitar and synth, Lynn Nicholson (also of Land of the Living and Chanterelles) on drums, and John Goforth on keyboards. Sinless will follow up the 2015 ‘Ethereality’ EP with the ‘Melodie’ EP, released on Curly Cassettes in October 2016.
